<Layout
	title="About Us"
	description="About the IEEE Signal Processing Society CMRIT Chapter"
>
	<h2>Who We Are</h2>
	<p>
		The IEEE Signal Processing Society (SPS) CMRIT Chapter is a student-run technical society at
		CMR Institute of Technology, Bangalore. Founded in 2025, we are part of the larger IEEE CMRIT
		student branch and focus on signal processing, image processing, and related engineering fields.
	</p>

	<h2>Our Mission</h2>
	<p>
		We aim to bridge the gap between academic learning and real-world engineering by hosting
		workshops, publishing research, and connecting students with industry professionals and IEEE
		members worldwide.
	</p>

	<h2>What We Do</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Host technical workshops and hands-on seminars</li>
		<li>Publish research posters and papers</li>
		<li>Organize guest lectures from industry experts</li>
		<li>Participate in IEEE conferences and competitions</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Contact Us</h2>
	<p>
		Interested in joining or collaborating? Reach out to us at
		<a href="mailto:ieeesps@cmrit.ac.in">ieeesps@cmrit.ac.in</a>
	</p>
</Layout>
